title: Devita, Hellman, and Rosenberg's cancer: principles & practice of oncology
abstract: "Cancer: Principles and Practice of Oncology presents the practicing oncologist with the practical as well as cutting-edge information needed to ensure the best possible care for each individual patient. To ensure a balanced multidisciplinary approach, a surgeon, a medical oncologist, and a radiation oncologist author each of the major treatment chapters. Each of the major treatment sections is preceded by an updated, brief chapter describing the molecular biology of that cancer and the prospects this new information holds for the improved management of cancer patients"--

title: Somatic versus germinal mutation
container-title: An Introduction to Genetic Analysis. 7th edition
abstract: Genes and chromosomes can mutate in either somatic or germinal tissue, and these changes are called somatic mutations and germinal mutations, respectively. These two different types are shown diagrammatically in Figure 15-3.Figure 15-3Somatic mutations are not transmitted to progeny, but germinal mutations may be transmitted to some or all progeny.
